---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import TeamCard from '../components/TeamCard.astro';
import TeamMemberModal from '../components/TeamMemberModal.astro';
import { teamMembers } from '../data/team';
---

<Layout title="About - Probably Fine Studios">
	<Nav />

	<section class="py-20 bg-black">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

			<!-- Header -->
			<div class="text-center mb-12">
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">About</h1>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-400">
					The talented <span class="relative inline-block mr-2"><span class="line-through text-red-500">people</span><span class="text-red-500 italic absolute -bottom-6 left-0 rotate-[-6deg] whitespace-nowrap">person</span></span> behind Probably Fine Studios
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Team -->
			<div class="flex justify-center mb-16">
				<div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 max-w-md w-full">
					{teamMembers.map(member => (
						<>
							<TeamCard
								name={member.name}
								role={member.role}
								bio={member.bio}
								image={member.image}
								memberId={member.id}
							/>
							<TeamMemberModal
								member={member}
								modalId={`modal-${member.id}`}
								isOpen={false}
							/>
						</>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Divider -->
			<div class="border-t border-gray-800 mb-16"></div>

			<!-- About content -->
			<div class="space-y-8">
				<!-- Who We Are -->
				<div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-800">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Who We Are</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
						Probably Fine Studios is a one-person digital studio — Chris at the helm, building apps, tools, and products around ideas that feel worth building, using whatever combination of code, AI, and stubbornness gets the job done.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-300">
						The name is honest. Nothing here claims to be perfect — but the work ships, the products are real, and they're probably fine.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- The Origin -->
				<div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-800">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-white">How We Got Here</h2>
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div class="flex gap-4">
							<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-2 rounded-full" style="background: #d6d3d1"></div>
							<div>
								<strong class="text-white text-lg block mb-1">ChrisOCPhoto — The Original</strong>
								<p class="text-gray-400">It started with photography. ChrisOCPhoto has been the home base for a long time — a personal portfolio built from scratch because nothing else felt right for the work. It's still going, still the OG.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex gap-4">
							<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-2 rounded-full" style="background: #e879f9"></div>
							<div>
								<strong class="text-white text-lg block mb-1">ChrisOCDigital — Where the Code Started</strong>
								<p class="text-gray-400">ChrisOCDigital grew out of that same creative energy, born when the code side kicked in. What started as building a better photography site turned into tools, scripts, programs, and experiments — a whole body of work taking shape under one roof. It was the pre-rebuild of ChrisOCPhoto and the stepping stone before Probably Fine Studios existed.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex gap-4">
							<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-2 rounded-full" style="background: #8b5cf6"></div>
							<div>
								<strong class="text-white text-lg block mb-1">Probably Fine Studios — The Next Step</strong>
								<p class="text-gray-400">When the projects needed a proper home, Probably Fine Studios became that. A studio name for a body of work that had quietly grown into something real — recipe apps, maps, weather dashboards, field tools, a browser game, and more. Built with AI, shipped with care.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- The Work -->
				<div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-800">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-white">The Work</h2>
					<div class="space-y-4">
						<div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500 pl-4">
							<strong class="text-white">ChrisOCPhoto & ChrisOCDigital</strong>
							<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">The originals — a photography portfolio and the creative digital space where the code journey began.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500 pl-4">
							<strong class="text-white">CookBookVerse & Editly</strong>
							<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">A recipe platform that feels like a real cookbook, and an AI photo editing tool built around the photographer's workflow.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500 pl-4">
							<strong class="text-white">FieldKit & Wandr</strong>
							<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Sharp field data collection tools and a location discovery app for when you're somewhere new and actually want to explore.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="border-l-2 border-indigo-500 pl-4">
							<strong class="text-white">Mapit, URBN Weather & Scramble</strong>
							<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Location data visualisation, an urban real-time safety dashboard, and a browser platformer built in Phaser with a very opinionated egg.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>
	</section>

	<Footer />
</Layout>
